# Functional Requirements Document (FRD) — <initiative name>

> Index: [`README.md`](./README.md) • Requirements: [`srs.md`](./srs.md)
> Created: <YYYY-MM-DD> • Last updated: <YYYY-MM-DD>

The **detailed functional behavior** behind the SRS requirements that need elaboration. This
*deepens* the SRS; it does not introduce new requirements (those belong in `srs.md`). Each section
references the SRS ID it elaborates.

> **Omit this document** (note the omission in `README.md`) if the SRS already captures the
> functional detail — common for small tools. Don't pad it to look complete.

## How to read this

Each feature is specified as: a short description, the **primary (happy) flow**, **alternate
flows**, **exception/failure flows**, and **field/validation rules**. Steps are observable — a tester
should be able to execute them.

